patch:
IPMI: Fix oops on ipmi_msghandler removal for non ipmi systems

When the ipmi_si module is loaded on a system without any ipmi device, it fails
with nodev. It would be fine if all resources were freed. A call to 
device_unregister() is missing, resulting to a oops when you remove the 
ipmi_msghandler.


Signed-Off-by: Arnaud Patard <apatard@mandriva.com>

---

Index: linux-2.6.17/drivers/char/ipmi/ipmi_si_intf.c
===================================================================
--- linux-2.6.17.orig/drivers/char/ipmi/ipmi_si_intf.c
+++ linux-2.6.17/drivers/char/ipmi/ipmi_si_intf.c
@@ -2549,6 +2549,7 @@ static __devinit int init_ipmi_si(void)
 #ifdef CONFIG_PCI
 		pci_unregister_driver(&ipmi_pci_driver);
 #endif
+		driver_unregister(&ipmi_driver);
 		printk("ipmi_si: Unable to find any System Interface(s)\n");
 		return -ENODEV;
 	} else {
